bug.short_desc: timeout handling bug: Uncaught SyntaxError: Unexpected end of input

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1070 bug investigation by Chrome development tools
Bug conditions: While sending AJAX request with timeout set and Json parser, in case when timeout actually appears, we got following exception: Uncaught SyntaxError: Unexpected end of input (look at Screenshot_1.png)
Investigation: As you can see on Screenshot_2.png, we tried to parse empty response body. In callstack you can see the reason why we are here is __onTimeout. Higher at the callstack (Screenshot_3.png) you can see that the reason we starting to parse response is qx.util.Request.isSuccessful and our response is timed out (Screenshot_4.png).
Maybe it would be better if qx.util.Request.isSuccessful checks is request timed out?..
*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of bug 5626 ***
Thanks for your detailed report. This bug has already been fixed in trunk.
Closed all bugs already shipped with a release.
